RACE.FOOTNOTES: KALIK tracked in the two path early, tipped out to the four path and was roused around the far turn, took aim from the six path into the stretch, was rallying while tipping slightly inwards through the stretch, got bumped by an inner foe while closing in near the finish, but got up on the wire to win. CUMBERLAND set the pace inside of rivals just off the rail around the two path, was coaxed into the far turn and under a ride while floating out to the four path at the top of the lane, dug in but veered out twice in the final furlong bumping an outer foe, but was nailed by that foe on the wire to place. HARDY CHOICE broke out and brushed with an outer foe, was steadied midway around the first turn while between foes in the three path and was wellback in the two path down the backside, was roused while tipping out passing the quarter pole and was in the six path entering the stretch, and kept on for show. FORGE IN FIRE was out in the five path around the first turn and trailed in the four path down the backstretch, was driven from the six path turning into the stretch, but finished evenly. LEFTEMBEHIND brushed with an inner foe at the start, raced off the pace in the three path, was under rousing around the far turn and urged from the eighth path at the top of the lane, lugged in in upper stretch and flattened in the final furlong. WIMHOF settled in midfield around the two path, lost ground along the rail rounding the far turn, was short of room turning into the lane and angled out to the five path, but was unable to factor. CERTAIN prompted the pace in the three path but faded in the stretch. ODE TO WAR chased around the four path but never threatened. AMERICA'S GUEST stalked around the three path early but yielded turning into the lane. WINDSOR PARK raced in midpack around the three path but was never a menace. NO CHANGES WERE MADE AFTER A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS HELD TO LOOK AT THE STRETCH RUN,
